# Data Flow Patterns

## Server Component vs Client Component

### Use Server Component (default) when:

- No interactivity needed
- No React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`)
- No browser APIs (`localStorage`, `window`)
- Want fast initial load with no loading states
- SEO important

### Use Client Component when:

- Need interactivity (forms, buttons with `onClick`)
- Need React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useContext`)
- Need browser APIs (`localStorage`, `window`, `document`)
- Need real-time updates (Convex subscriptions)

## Common Data Flow Patterns

### Server Component → Display Data

Fast initial render, no loading state, SEO-friendly.

```ts
// app/items/page.tsx (Server Component)
import { ItemList } from '@/components/items/item-list';
import { getItems } from '@/lib/features/items/queries';

export default async function ItemsPage() {
  const items = await getItems();
  return <ItemList items={items} />;
}
```

### Client Component → Real-time Updates

Subscribe to Convex for real-time updates.

```ts
// app/dashboard/page.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
import { useMyItems } from '@/lib/features/items/hooks';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  const items = useMyItems();

  if (!items) {
    return <div>Loading...</div>
  };

  return <ItemList items={items} />;
}
```

### Hybrid Pattern → Best of Both

Server renders initial data, client subscribes for updates.

```ts
// app/items/page.tsx (Server Component)
import { getItems } from '@/lib/features/items/queries';
import { ItemsClient } from './items-client';

export default async function ItemsPage() {
  const initialItems = await getItems();
  return <ItemsClient initialData={initialItems} />;
}

// app/items/items-client.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
import { useItems } from '@/lib/features/items/hooks';
import { ItemList } from '@/components/items/item-list';

export function ItemsClient({ initialData }) {
  const items = useItems() ?? initialData;
  return <ItemList items={items} />;
}
```

### Form Submission → Server Action

Handle form submissions with Server Actions.

```ts
// app/items/new/page.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';
import { createItem } from '@/lib/features/items/actions';

export default function NewItemPage() {
  const router = useRouter();

  const handleSubmit = async (data) => {
    await createItem(data);
    router.push('/items');
  };

  return <ItemForm onSubmit={handleSubmit} />;
}
```

### Button Click → Client Mutation

Quick interactions use client-side mutations.

```ts
// components/items/favorite-button.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
import { useFavoriteToggle } from '@/lib/features/favorites/hooks';

export function FavoriteButton({ itemId }) {
  const toggleFavorite = useFavoriteToggle();

  const handleClick = async () => {
    await toggleFavorite({ itemId });
  };

  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Favorite</button>;
}
```

## Convex Data Fetching Patterns

### Decision Tree: When to Use Each Pattern

**Use `preloadQuery` + `usePreloadedQuery` when:**
- Critical above-the-fold content (homepage, landing pages)
- SEO is important (public pages, content indexing)
- Want zero loading states for initial render
- Need both server rendering and client interactivity

**Use `fetchQuery` (server-only) when:**
- Static data that doesn't change during user session
- No client-side interactivity needed
- SEO critical but no real-time updates required

**Use `useQuery` hooks when:**
- User-specific data (favorites, profiles, dashboard content)
- Need real-time updates during user session
- Interactive features that respond to user actions
- Not SEO critical (behind auth, user-specific)

### Pattern Examples

```ts
// ✅ Hybrid: preloadQuery + usePreloadedQuery
// app/page.tsx (Server Component)
export default async function HomePage() {
  const preloadedItems = await preloadQuery(
    api.items.list,
    { limit: 12 },
    { token: authToken },
  );
  return <HomeContent preloadedItems={preloadedItems} />;
}

// app/_components/home-content.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
export function HomeContent({ preloadedItems }) {
  const initialItems = usePreloadedQuery(preloadedItems);
  // Add interactivity: pagination, filtering, real-time updates
}
```

```ts
// ✅ Server-only: fetchQuery
// app/items/[slug]/page.tsx (Server Component)
export default async function ItemPage({ params }) {
  const itemData = await fetchQuery(
    api.items.getBySlug,
    { slug: params.slug },
    { token: authToken },
  );
  
  if (!itemData) notFound();
  
  // Render directly - static content, SEO critical
  return <ItemContent data={itemData} />;
}
```

```ts
// ✅ Client-only: useQuery hooks
// lib/features/users/hooks/use-favorites.ts
export function useFavorites(limit?: number) {
  const data = useQuery(api.users.getFavorites, { limit });
  return { data, isLoading: data === undefined };
}
```

### Quick Decision Matrix

| Scenario | Pattern | Rationale |
|----------|---------|-----------|
| **Homepage/data listing** | `preloadQuery` + `usePreloadedQuery` | Zero loading states and real-time updates |
| **Public content** | `fetchQuery` only | SEO critical and static content |
| **User dashboard/favorites** | `useQuery` hooks | User-specific data and real-time updates |
| **Interactive lists** | Hybrid pattern | Best performance and user experience |

## Authentication Patterns

### Server Component Protection

```ts
import { getServerSession } from '@/lib/services/auth/server';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';

export default async function ProtectedPage() {
  const session = await getServerSession();

  if (!session) {
    redirect('/auth/login');
  }

  return <div>Protected content</div>;
}
```

### Client Component Session

```ts
'use client';
import { useSession } from '@/lib/services/auth/client';

export function UserProfile() {
  const session = useSession();

  if (!session) {
    return <div>Please log in</div>;
  }

  return <div>Welcome {session.user.name}</div>;
}
```

## Best Practices

### Start with Server Components

```ts
// ✅ Default to Server Component
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <Display data={data} />;
}
```

Only go client when you need interactivity, hooks, browser APIs, or real-time updates.

### Keep Routes Thin

```ts
// ✅ Business logic in hooks/utils
export default function ItemsPage() {
  const items = usePublicItems();
  return <ItemList items={items} />;
}

// ❌ Business logic in routes
export default function ItemsPage() {
  const items = useQuery(api.items.list);
  const filtered = items?.filter((i) => i.isPublic && !i.archived);
  const sorted = filtered?.sort((a, b) => b._creationTime - a._creationTime);
  // ...
}
```
